This gives parents one more day to apply for school placements for their children. JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng Education Department has confirmed that the online school admissions system for grades one and eight will be closing on Monday.This gives parents one more day to apply for school placements for their children.The department says those who don't apply online will be placed by the department wherever there is space.The department's Steve Mabona said, We encourage those that have not applied to do so because we are not going to have an extension, which means by July to October we will be placing those that need to be placed. 